---
import SeriesIndexImage from '../assets/og-default.png';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';

// The hub-of-hubs. Add a series here when its hub page goes live.
const series = [
	{
		href: '/blog/kubernetes-series/',
		name: 'Kubernetes on k3s',
		status: 'in progress',
		blurb:
			'Learn Kubernetes the way it sticks, by running it on one cheap node. Your first Deployment and the reconciliation loop, then config, storage, health checks, and Ingress.',
	},
	{
		href: '/blog/claude-code-skills/',
		name: 'Claude Code skills',
		status: '4 skills',
		blurb:
			'Four skills that chain into one pipeline: spot the repeatable work, map the codebase read-only, turn it into a locked plan, and hand that plan to worker models.',
	},
	{
		href: '/blog/pong-series/',
		name: 'Pong in LÖVE and Lua',
		status: '5 parts',
		blurb:
			'Build Pong from a blank window into a juicy arcade cabinet with LÖVE and Lua. Two-player game, a computer opponent, a predictive AI, an attract mode, and power-ups. One main.lua, no engine.',
	},
];
---

<Layout
	title="Series — Peculiar Engineer"
	description="The multi-part guides on Peculiar Engineer: hands-on series on Kubernetes and k3s, building games in LÖVE and Lua, and the Claude Code skills I've built. Start at the beginning, or jump to the part you need."
	kind="page"
	showDate={false}
	heroImage={SeriesIndexImage}
>
	<p class="whoami"><span class="prompt">~/$</span> ls series/</p>

	<p>
		Most posts here are a single fix you can land and leave. These are the longer runs: a
		subject taken from nothing to something real, one part at a time. Each series has its own
		hub with the parts in order, so you can start at the beginning or drop into the one you
		came for.
	</p>

	<ol class="parts">
		{
			series.map((s) => (
				<li class="part done">
					<span class="badge live">{s.status}</span>
					<a href={s.href}>{s.name}</a>
					<p>{s.blurb}</p>
				</li>
			))
		}
	</ol>

	<p class="closing">
		More series land here as they grow. If one saved you an afternoon, that is the point.
	</p>
</Layout>

<style>
	.whoami {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		color: var(--sys-dim);
		margin-bottom: 1.5em;
	}
	.whoami .prompt {
		color: var(--sys-fg);
		font-weight: 700;
	}
	.parts {
		list-style: none;
		margin: 1.5em 0;
		padding: 0;
	}
	.part {
		border: 1px solid var(--sys-dim);
		border-left: 3px solid var(--sys-fg);
		padding: 1em 1.2em;
		margin: 0 0 1em;
	}
	.part .badge {
		display: inline-block;
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.06em;
		color: var(--sys-fg);
		margin-bottom: 0.4em;
	}
	.part a {
		display: block;
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-weight: 700;
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}
	.part p {
		margin: 0.4em 0 0;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		color: var(--sys-text);
	}
	.closing {
		margin-top: 1.5em;
	}
</style>
